<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-08-21T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-08-21T11:00:00-05:00" n="647" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d647">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/2937: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-08-22T01:00:00+09:00"><hi rend="italic">August
                                            22, 1920—1 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 6:12
                                    a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>432. Your 286 July 27, 5 p.m. Minister for Foreign Affairs
                                acknowledges receipt of information contained in your telegram
                                referred to above and adds that, inasmuch as matter will be
                                presumably submitted to the consideration [of] the proposed
                                conference of groups’ representatives to be held in New York next
                                autumn, he may have occasion to offer some observation on this
                                subject when the result of its consideration by the conference is
                                known.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bell</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>